Definition : INT_MULT_FLOAT_TRUNC(int i, float f)

Defined in : #include <math.h>

Description: Multiplies an integer with a float, and truncates the results to
             the nearest integer.
                INT_MULT_FLOAT_ROUND(1000, 0.3764)  ->  366
                INT_MULT_FLOAT_ROUND(1000, 0.3765)  ->  366

Arguments  : int i - the integer.
             int f - the float.

Returns    : int - the result of the calculation.

See also   : INT_MULT_FLOAT_ROUND and INT_MULT_FLOAT
